    <h3 class="title"><a href="/articles/diylighting#comment-3420" class="active">Hot lights to cold</a></h3>
    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Demosthien (not verified) on Sun, 2009-05-03 23:50.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>If you're comfortable (&amp; knowledgable) enough it is a simple matter to remove the halogen lamp fittings &amp; replace them with standard household bulb fittings. Once that's done you can use Compact Fluorescant Lights (CFL). These can be easily found in daylight balanced versions &amp; they're cool (to the touch). Think DIY Spiderlites!</p>
<p>WARNING: DO NOT MESS WITH THE WIRING &amp; ELECTRICS UNLESS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING.</p>
