<a id="comment-940"></a>
  <div class="comment styledbox">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/articles/diylighting#comment-940" class="active">Regarding white balance,</a></h3>
    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Anonymous (not verified) on Fri, 2008-01-18 18:05.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Regarding white balance, halogen lighting isn't all that bad if you shoot digitally. Just be sure to shoot in RAW, and you can set the WB as needed in PP. You can also shoot a gray or white card and use that to set the WB. No need for special bulbs at all.</p>
</div>
