<div style="margin-left:25px;">
<a id="comment-3616"></a>
  <div class="comment styledbox">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/articles/diylighting#comment-3616" class="active">What about dimming?</a></h3>
    <div class="submitted">Submitted by Rocky (not verified) on Sun, 2009-08-09 09:42.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Don't try to dim incandescent lights. As you dim them they colour-shift drastically towards yellow. </p>
<p>If you want to drop the light level, either buy a lower rated globe (these linear halogens come and various ratings from 100W up to 500W) or simply move the light further away. The inverse-square law is your friend.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links"><a href="/comment/reply/19/3616">reply</a></div>
  </div>
